µJEEntry #7 "Lost" by µC5Farfar/Loonies:µC4 A shipwreck in an icy world. This image is actually a lot better than it looked to me the first time I saw it on the big screen. Perhaps I was too far away from the screen to see all the details, as there is a lot to discover here. Judging from the steps that I saw Farfar started the image with a Maya model of a ship and later used a paint-program to improve the ship and create an icy world around it. To enhance the feeling of depth in the image a wooden pole sticks into the ice in the foreground. A very nice detail in my opinion that from this wooden pole a little (religious) cross is hanging; just like the sailers that lost their ship here fought hard to survive. The image doesn't show if they made it or not :-)

Entry #8 "IceMC in Ice Land" by µC5DiamonDie/foobug & Numedia Cyclops:µC4 Here the "Ice" theme is twisted into something that doesn't have to do with frozen water. The image shows a Jamaican guy with a lot of white powder in his moustache and hair. Either the powder is drugs-related or this guy has a serious dandruff problem. The image itself is not very special quality-wise, it looks like it was build up from zero with a tablet.

Entry #10 "Frozen Moment" by µC5Critikill/fr/mwi/scn:µC4 This is a typical Critikill image - actually these are two seemingly unrelated images, which are joined together into one scene. Both parts of the image show girls, one part shows a girls face with some ice hanging from the mouth and nose, the other part shows a girl who looks like she is trying to escape from the ice but is instead frozen in the moment...

When I first saw the image on the big screen I thought that Critikill used a blue filter to create an ice-effect on an image he had lying around, but now that I saw the steps I have to admit that I think these image were created especially for the ice theme compo at Breakpoint. 

Entry #14 "Iceplanet Patrol" by µC5Acryl/Haujobb:µC4 "Houston, we have a winner". The results aren't in until tomorrow, but I wouldn't mind betting some money that this entry will win the Theme compo this year. This 24bit image depicts a fantasy-scene where a sentry of some sort is sitting on a huge icecreature - I was immediately reminded of an image I saw in a PC-demo from the early ninetees with a female sentry in the same setting. Not that this image is a ripoff of that image in any way, this was just my first impression. The characters in the image are well-positioned which shows that Acryl is really a professional. What I really like in this image (and in any image) is that although the image has black borders, some details of the image flow into the black borders of the image. One of the claws of the ice-creature for example, or a rock in the foreground. A must-see image.

