Entry #1 "Monsterball" by µC5Helge/hjb:µC4 First image in this compo and I am immediately in the mood. Please let me describe the contents of this image. Imagine a little red and skinny monster with a mouth full of razorsharp and bloody teeth that has killed the easterbunny and has used the ears from the bunny on his own head. Now this monster is offering the viewer an easteregg. And look at the technique used in this image to create the impression of rounded surfaces, I like this.

Entry #3 "Dpaint 4 Ever" by µC5Tof/Drifters:µC4 Ahhh, an 8 bit entry. I love 8 bit. As the title suggests this image is created in DPaint and I believe it. The image shows two girls in a landscape, and one girl looks like she is about to knight the other girl with her big sword. Shading is all wrong, the posture of the characters is wrong and so is the depth in the image. But I think this is a fun image anyway.

Entry #5 "hide and seek" by µC5cp/farbrausch:µC4 A girl is hiding from a big and evil monster. Although I like this image it feels unfinished to me. Perhaps that is why the image is so dark, to avoid drawing too much attention to unfinished details?

Entry #7 "The Last Stand" by µC5xeNusion:µC4 An image that has a WW-II atmosphere, it shows fighterplanes in action. The image has an incredible amount of small details, especially in the background. In the background you can see people parachuting from planes, and there is a complete city in the background as well. What can I say about this image? I really admire the effort that must have gone into it! There are so many details that it must have cost many, many hours to create the image. As with many images with this much detail all the small objects seem a bit unfinished.

Entry #14 "In The Dark" by µC5Visualice:µC4 A typical Visualice entry and I like it. If you only look at the image briefly you will see a girl in a dark fantasy setting, but look closer and you will see some nifty details in the dark.

Entry #16 "Dark moon dragon" by µC5Sly:µC4 This image shows a female jester. It is actually based on a character from a playstation game called Chrono cross. Some of the parts in this image are extremely detailed, but other parts look unfinished to me. Overall this image doesn't make a big impression on me, but I can't put my finger on the reason for it because the image in itself is good.

Entry #18 "The last Peacebringer" by µC5Critikill/fr & mwi & scn:µC4 This image by Critikill is made up of two parts again, but now the separate parts seem to be much more related to each other. The image shows two women, one is handing a peace pigeon to the other. The pigeon is bleeding and one of the women is showing a stigmata. The overal atmosphere is pretty grim. Altough the two parts of the image are more related this time, I don't have the feeling both parts make one coherent whole image. Some parts of the image are definately better as other parts, but that doesn't matter since the viewers attention is drawn towards the pigeon anyway.

When I viewed the graphics on my own machine I noticed another female face in the clouds, and I have to admit that I hadn't noticed that face on the bigscreen.

Entry #21 "Dragon G" by µC5Fireball/Nuance^Scarab:µC4 The second and best 8bit image from the compo. I've got to hand it to Fireball that I am always looking forward to his next image. This image shows a cartoonish dragon on one side and a girls face on the other. Both parts of the image are unrelated to me, but the combination doesn't bother me that much. The edge between both parts in the image is a bit 'sudden' though, almost like there was not enough time to create the edge he had planned to create. 

Entry #23 "Me, the Beast" by µC5Raven/Nuance:µC4 Another multipart image, again a girl's face and a dragon. Unlike Fireball's entry the dragon in this image is not cartoonish, but looks more serious. Raven made a great effort of using contrasting colors to make this image jump straight in your face. As far as I am concerned he succeeded.

Entry #25 "Arrrrrrrr" by µC5Acryl/Haujobb:µC4 Does this guy every stop overflowing us with quality images?! This entry is just as good as his entry in the theme compo, and it uses very similar tricks and techniques as the other image. There are also parts in this image that overlap the black borders, for example. What the image depicts is a bunch of skeleton pirates (hence the title, matey!).

Usually scene images in compos have one single detail that attracts the viewers attention, the image must not be too complicated or voters like you and me will not remember the image. Unlike his Iceplanet patrol image in the theme compo this image has multiple parts that caught my attention. Lets just state that this image is very good as well and that you must see it. His images are incredible to me, but somehow I hope that Acryl doesn't win in both compo's...

Entry #27 "Me and Louie's Sister" by µC5Wade/Haujobb&Fairlight:µC4 Most sceners will know the famous image from the mid-ninetees "Me and my little sister" by Louie from The Black Lotus. This image by Wade is a tribute to that particular image by Louie. It shows the faces of some guy and Louie's sister who is now a couple of years older and a couple of years more attractive. It is a good image, but I think that Wade must have used a photo to create an image of this quality. If the photo was only used as reference then I don't mind too much - unfortunately the steps provided with the image do not give me a definate answer on this subject.

That's it. I wanted to write my impressions about the entries in the wild compo and the C64 entries as well, but there is not enough time left for that. I hope you had fun reading my first impressions about these compo images, maybe my opinion on them will change once I get some sleep. The graphics I mentioned above, and some of the graphics I didn't write about, will find their way onto the gfxzone somewhere in the next week. Live long and pixel!
